The textbook is a great idea! I'm sure you will make great progress over time. Do you have any tips for other people who are learning English?
What words should they focus on first?

User:
I would recommend using Duolingo as a really useful resource. It's easy to access, and it provides small, achievable goals. Also, always use context clues to figure out the meaning of new words if you're not sure how to pronounce them.